-- Amtrak Proposes Two New Rail Tunnels from New Jersey to NY
-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 2011-02-07T16:10:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-07/amtrak-proposes-two-new-rail-tunnels-from-new-jersey-to-ny.html
  Amtrak  is proposing to spend $50
million to begin preliminary engineering and design on two new
rail tunnels from  New Jersey  to  New York City .  The tunnels would increase commuter train capacity by
allowing  New Jersey Transit  to add 13 trains per peak hour into
New York City and Amtrak to add eight. Amtrak projects the
tunnel project could be completed in 2020 at an estimated cost
of $13.5 billion. The information was released in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Heather Burke at 
 hburke2@bloomberg.net  